WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.340 --> 00:00:08.058
Prof: Last time we
started talking about tropical

00:00:08.058 --> 00:00:13.121
places where high productivity
agriculture is generally just

00:00:13.121 --> 00:00:14.580
not possible.
 

00:00:14.580 --> 00:00:19.914
Hence, without productive
agriculture you can't support

00:00:19.914 --> 00:00:21.890
dense populations.
 

00:00:21.890 --> 00:00:27.885
Those cultures grew up in
time--in places where plenty of

00:00:27.885 --> 00:00:34.630
land, land was not filled up,
it was people that were scarce.

00:00:34.630 --> 00:00:37.676
While individual women of
course still had to control

00:00:37.676 --> 00:00:40.020
their fertility so that the
children--

00:00:40.020 --> 00:00:43.628
the infants that they had
didn't die and there's many,

00:00:43.628 --> 00:00:46.080
many things that they do for
that.

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:50.152
The community cultural controls
on fertility are generally

00:00:50.152 --> 00:00:53.725
absent because from the
community point of view you

00:00:53.725 --> 00:00:56.485
always wants to be,
at that time,

00:00:56.485 --> 00:01:01.313
larger and among other reasons
to protect your community from

00:01:01.313 --> 00:01:06.060
the ravages of hostile neighbors
because almost all of these

00:01:06.060 --> 00:01:10.459
communities are--
just read any history of any

00:01:10.459 --> 00:01:14.590
part of the world constant,
constant warfare,

00:01:14.590 --> 00:01:17.220
as we've discussed a lot.
 

00:01:17.220 --> 00:01:21.021
Of many places in the world,
which one could describe,

00:01:21.021 --> 00:01:25.253
traditional Africa provides
some of the best examples of how

00:01:25.253 --> 00:01:27.188
these cultures operate.
 

00:01:27.188 --> 00:01:29.659
Again, I want to emphasize that
this a tradition--

00:01:29.659 --> 00:01:33.325
a picture of a traditional time
and things are changing now

00:01:33.325 --> 00:01:36.170
extremely rapidly everywhere in
the world,

00:01:36.170 --> 00:01:39.000
including of course Africa.
 

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:44.446
As I showed you last time,
Africa really is different than

00:01:44.446 --> 00:01:46.739
the rest of the world.
 

00:01:46.739 --> 00:01:50.525
I showed statistics comparing
Morocco on the north coast of

00:01:50.525 --> 00:01:54.050
Africa, included in the
Mediterranean cultural zone.

00:01:54.050 --> 00:01:57.132
You cross the Sahara,
you're in Niger,

00:01:57.132 --> 00:02:00.382
or you're in Mali,
and totally different

00:02:00.382 --> 00:02:01.549
situation.
 

00:02:01.549 --> 00:02:03.920
The number of children is much
high--

00:02:03.920 --> 00:02:06.700
people have is much higher,
I showed you that,

00:02:06.700 --> 00:02:09.020
the number of children that
they want is much higher,

00:02:09.020 --> 00:02:12.120
infant mortality has come down
in both places,

00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:14.818
in Morocco the fertility
responds to it,

00:02:14.818 --> 00:02:19.979
in Niger the fertility does not
respond to it.

00:02:19.979 --> 00:02:26.293
While we're going--so we're
going to discuss this region and

00:02:26.293 --> 00:02:31.858
using a lot of generalizations
which will not fit any

00:02:31.858 --> 00:02:34.318
particular culture.
 

00:02:34.318 --> 00:02:39.989
If you add up all the birthrate
statistics, Sub-Saharan African

00:02:39.989 --> 00:02:44.470
has about twice the birth rate
of North Africa.

00:02:44.470 --> 00:02:46.400
Again, it's all Suni Muslim
we're talking about,

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:49.024
so religion is not the
difference, but the something

00:02:49.024 --> 00:02:52.370
else about the southern culture
which we've been talking about.

00:02:52.370 --> 00:02:57.428
It probably starts with the
agriculture and then goes into

00:02:57.428 --> 00:02:58.758
other fields.
 

00:02:58.758 --> 00:03:03.960
Of all the things that are
changing in Africa,

00:03:03.960 --> 00:03:06.840
fertility--the attitudes toward
fertility--

00:03:06.840 --> 00:03:09.825
again I'm always using
fertility as the number of

00:03:09.825 --> 00:03:13.311
children a woman actually has
and not her ability to have

00:03:13.311 --> 00:03:14.120
children.
 

00:03:14.120 --> 00:03:17.252
The attitudes towards fertility
are sort of the most resistant

00:03:17.252 --> 00:03:17.870
to change.
 

00:03:17.870 --> 00:03:22.370
These societies have what you
might call a culture of

00:03:22.370 --> 00:03:27.650
reproduction in which the
central idea is that of lineage,

00:03:27.650 --> 00:03:30.979
a family and its line of male
ancestors.

00:03:30.979 --> 00:03:35.840
The prime duty in these
cultures is to keep the lineage

00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:36.560
going.
 

00:03:36.560 --> 00:03:39.560
Of course you've all read stuff
about China, China is

00:03:39.560 --> 00:03:42.789
not--traditional China is not
particularly different than

00:03:42.789 --> 00:03:43.310
this.
 

00:03:43.310 --> 00:03:47.470
The important thing is to
provide descendants for the

00:03:47.470 --> 00:03:48.430
ancestors.
 

00:03:48.430 --> 00:03:51.721
Not only is your own future--if
you don't have the son as your

00:03:51.721 --> 00:03:55.077
own future as a shade,
as sort of a spirit that hovers

00:03:55.077 --> 00:03:57.610
around,
is dependent on continuation of

00:03:57.610 --> 00:03:58.240
the line.
 

00:03:58.240 --> 00:04:01.735
The whole history of ancestors,
stretching back,

00:04:01.735 --> 00:04:04.860
is dependent on your having
descendants.

00:04:04.860 --> 00:04:09.744
The future line which is
perceived as sort of almost in

00:04:09.744 --> 00:04:12.598
existence,
of potential existence,

00:04:12.598 --> 00:04:16.980
the whole line from the distant
past going through you to the

00:04:16.980 --> 00:04:21.509
distant future is all dependent
on you having descendants,

00:04:21.509 --> 00:04:24.810
male descendants in the line.
 

00:04:24.810 --> 00:04:28.290
The central purpose,
the central goal,

00:04:28.290 --> 00:04:33.463
the central job of existence is
to continue this line of

00:04:33.463 --> 00:04:34.779
fertility.
 

00:04:34.779 --> 00:04:42.649
Now the traditional religion is
based on this lineage idea.

00:04:42.649 --> 00:04:47.557
Because it's your own--the gods
are in a sense your own

00:04:47.557 --> 00:04:49.500
ancestors,
people that you knew,

00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:52.971
people that you talk too,
they stay more close to you

00:04:52.971 --> 00:04:54.449
after they die.
 

00:04:54.449 --> 00:04:58.930
Unlike Western gods where you
pray but it's never clear

00:04:58.930 --> 00:05:03.079
whether your prayers are being
answered or not,

00:05:03.079 --> 00:05:07.146
in an ancestor worship
situation, the answer is right

00:05:07.146 --> 00:05:10.507
there,
and you can talk back and forth

00:05:10.507 --> 00:05:11.449
with them.
 

00:05:11.449 --> 00:05:14.834
They're not distant,
eerie, supernatural kind of

00:05:14.834 --> 00:05:19.083
characters but rather like a
grandfather who just stays near

00:05:19.083 --> 00:05:20.740
us after his death.
 

00:05:20.740 --> 00:05:24.718
This kind of description comes
from the ethnographers,

00:05:24.718 --> 00:05:29.072
the anthropologists that go and
talk to the people in these

00:05:29.072 --> 00:05:30.949
traditional cultures.
 

00:05:30.949 --> 00:05:33.149
The lineage head,
who is almost always the old--

00:05:33.149 --> 00:05:36.579
often the oldest male member of
the lineage,

00:05:36.579 --> 00:05:40.807
he often can communicate
directly with these ancestors or

00:05:40.807 --> 00:05:45.564
there may be a soothsayer in the
community and then the head man

00:05:45.564 --> 00:05:49.716
will commission the soothsayer
to ask the ancestors some

00:05:49.716 --> 00:05:51.680
particular question.
 

00:05:51.680 --> 00:05:55.084
The ancestors are quite
available to discuss the most

00:05:55.084 --> 00:05:58.949
ordinary and mundane issues of
life or they can discuss very

00:05:58.949 --> 00:06:00.259
weighty affairs.
 

00:06:00.259 --> 00:06:03.569
This doesn't require waiting
for some big holiday or some

00:06:03.569 --> 00:06:06.327
huge amount of time,
it can be--the whole thing can

00:06:06.327 --> 00:06:08.800
be transacted in 15 minutes or
maybe a half an hour.

00:06:08.800 --> 00:06:12.939
Sometimes they're contacted,
they provide their answers,

00:06:12.939 --> 00:06:16.100
and you've got the answer that
you need.

00:06:16.100 --> 00:06:18.129
One of the interesting,
with respect to this course,

00:06:18.129 --> 00:06:21.081
one of the interesting things
that goes on is that family

00:06:21.081 --> 00:06:23.399
planning is being introduced
into Africa,

00:06:23.399 --> 00:06:26.850
has been now for quite a while,
and it's becoming available.

00:06:26.850 --> 00:06:30.899
The people are thinking it
over; it's a hot topic.

00:06:30.899 --> 00:06:32.951
They're discussing it,
they're trying to figure out

00:06:32.951 --> 00:06:34.470
whether it's good for them or
not,

00:06:34.470 --> 00:06:37.170
whether it's permissible for
them or not,

00:06:37.170 --> 00:06:38.579
what's going to happen if you
use it,

00:06:38.579 --> 00:06:40.170
what's going to happen if you
don't use it.

00:06:40.170 --> 00:06:46.110
It's a very hot topic and of
course they want the wisdom of

00:06:46.110 --> 00:06:48.569
the ancestors on this.
 

00:06:48.569 --> 00:06:52.923
In the middle of this,
one set of demographers went

00:06:52.923 --> 00:06:55.911
into--
in Ghana there's a group of

00:06:55.911 --> 00:06:58.406
Nankana--
the name of the people there,

00:06:58.406 --> 00:07:01.533
and they went into their
villages and they wanted to see

00:07:01.533 --> 00:07:02.838
how this worked out.
 

00:07:02.838 --> 00:07:07.201
If this discussion with the
ancestors, as they call the

00:07:07.201 --> 00:07:10.274
traditional religion,
would be hostile to the

00:07:10.274 --> 00:07:13.286
introduction of family planning
because elsewhere in the world

00:07:13.286 --> 00:07:15.509
of course the more conservative
the more--

00:07:15.509 --> 00:07:17.750
it doesn't depend on the
individual religion,

00:07:17.750 --> 00:07:20.959
a particular religion as I have
said and will say again,

00:07:20.959 --> 00:07:23.949
but it does depend on the
religiosity of the person.

00:07:23.949 --> 00:07:26.819
The more religious a person is,
in almost any tradition,

00:07:26.819 --> 00:07:28.930
the more hostile they will be
to change,

00:07:28.930 --> 00:07:33.261
and in particular to the
adoption of new reproductive

00:07:33.261 --> 00:07:36.009
practices like family planning.
 

00:07:36.009 --> 00:07:39.247
They're interested in this
issue how this would work out in

00:07:39.247 --> 00:07:41.089
traditional villages in Africa.
 

00:07:41.089 --> 00:07:43.764
He asked the village head
man--one of the

00:07:43.764 --> 00:07:47.708
anthropologists--to inquire of
the spirits how many children

00:07:47.708 --> 00:07:51.240
should a family have;
a simple question.

00:07:51.240 --> 00:07:56.238
Here's what the spirit said,
"Listen to what I have to

00:07:56.238 --> 00:08:01.238
say, children are the lineage,
if there are no children the

00:08:01.238 --> 00:08:03.050
lineage will end.
 

00:08:03.050 --> 00:08:07.932
We ancestors want many children;
the women should give birth to

00:08:07.932 --> 00:08:09.439
many children."
 

00:08:09.439 --> 00:08:12.863
That was a pretty clear answer;
there was no futzing around

00:08:12.863 --> 00:08:13.959
with that one.
 

00:08:13.959 --> 00:08:17.646
But being Western skeptics,
they didn't really believe that

00:08:17.646 --> 00:08:21.161
the ancestor was saying that,
so he was saying,

00:08:21.161 --> 00:08:26.300
well the headman put into the
mouths of the spirits whatever

00:08:26.300 --> 00:08:29.865
the headman believed,
and that was not--made the

00:08:29.865 --> 00:08:32.158
anthropologists quite satisfied
with this.

00:08:32.158 --> 00:08:35.940
He was a good scientist and he
did the control experiment,

00:08:35.940 --> 00:08:38.509
he asked the headman,
the same headman who had just

00:08:38.509 --> 00:08:41.129
reported the conservative views
of the ancestors.

00:08:41.129 --> 00:08:44.035
Well what do you think,
he got a completely different

00:08:44.035 --> 00:08:44.538
answer.
 

00:08:44.538 --> 00:08:48.029
"Women need to have just
enough children.

00:08:48.029 --> 00:08:50.750
Currently it is very difficult
to fend for the children.

00:08:50.750 --> 00:08:52.928
There's no food to feed them.
 

00:08:52.928 --> 00:08:56.508
If they are in school it is
difficult to pay their school

00:08:56.508 --> 00:08:59.000
fees and to buy them school
uniforms.

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:02.125
Taking them to the hospital
when they are sick demands a lot

00:09:02.125 --> 00:09:02.710
of money.
 

00:09:02.710 --> 00:09:07.740
That is why we need to give
birth to few children."

00:09:07.740 --> 00:09:10.705
Well that's a little different
take, and so then the

00:09:10.705 --> 00:09:13.379
demographer's brain starts
rolling and says;

00:09:13.379 --> 00:09:15.879
now I got the scene,
now I got it right.

00:09:15.879 --> 00:09:18.879
The ancestors are giving the
traditional point of view,

00:09:18.879 --> 00:09:20.892
well that's true,
that was what the older

00:09:20.892 --> 00:09:24.129
generation believed,
but the headmen are part of the

00:09:24.129 --> 00:09:28.287
current generation and they're
going to take current views into

00:09:28.287 --> 00:09:31.440
consideration and take a more
moderate view.

00:09:31.440 --> 00:09:35.280
They interviewed the next--they
went to the next village and

00:09:35.280 --> 00:09:39.123
interviewed the next lineage
head and that hypothesis didn't

00:09:39.123 --> 00:09:39.970
stand up.
 

00:09:39.970 --> 00:09:42.231
Speaking for himself,
the headman said,

00:09:42.231 --> 00:09:45.804
"I would like them to have
many children because a large

00:09:45.804 --> 00:09:47.889
following it makes one a chief.
 

00:09:47.889 --> 00:09:49.918
There is power in numbers."
 

00:09:49.918 --> 00:09:52.931
This is the idea that if you
have only a few people in your

00:09:52.931 --> 00:09:54.798
village you're not very
powerful,

00:09:54.798 --> 00:09:56.808
your neighbors can ignore you,
they can take advantage of you,

00:09:56.808 --> 00:10:00.333
but if you have a big set of
descendants and a big family and

00:10:00.333 --> 00:10:03.291
extended family,
a big village then you're a

00:10:03.291 --> 00:10:07.110
powerful chief and he wanted
children so that he would be

00:10:07.110 --> 00:10:07.929
powerful.
 

00:10:14.120 --> 00:10:16.892
But then this same guy was
asked to see what the ancestors

00:10:16.892 --> 00:10:19.240
have to say about it,
and the ancestors said,

00:10:19.240 --> 00:10:22.168
"Everybody should have a
small number of children,

00:10:22.168 --> 00:10:26.918
but they should not refuse to
have children altogether."

00:10:26.918 --> 00:10:29.960
Since the ancestors are close
at hand,

00:10:29.960 --> 00:10:34.700
it's perfectly reasonable that
they're aware of current trends,

00:10:34.700 --> 00:10:38.191
and one of the ancestors said,
"It is now difficult to

00:10:38.191 --> 00:10:40.840
get an education as well as to
do farming.

00:10:40.840 --> 00:10:43.679
If a problem crops up and the
child is sick then money is

00:10:43.679 --> 00:10:44.340
everything.
 

00:10:44.340 --> 00:10:47.259
You have to buy medicine,"
meaning modern medicine,

00:10:47.259 --> 00:10:50.291
"And even if you go to the
herbalist,"

00:10:50.291 --> 00:10:53.011
traditional medicine,
"You need to take a

00:10:53.011 --> 00:10:54.820
fowl," a chicken or
something,

00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:56.450
"along to pay for the
treatment.

00:10:56.450 --> 00:11:00.086
It's no longer the same as in
the olden days when everybody

00:11:00.086 --> 00:11:01.340
did farming."
 

00:11:01.340 --> 00:11:05.211
That's the ancestor speaking,
very well aware of current

00:11:05.211 --> 00:11:06.759
trends and problems.
 

00:11:06.759 --> 00:11:10.027
After they interviewed a whole
lot of these Nankana villages in

00:11:10.027 --> 00:11:12.028
Ghana they summarized the
research,

00:11:12.028 --> 00:11:16.658
and the result was no pattern
of responses at all.

00:11:16.658 --> 00:11:20.759
Sometime the headman and his
ancestors they agreed;

00:11:20.759 --> 00:11:23.933
sometimes they disagreed;
sometimes it was the ancestor

00:11:23.933 --> 00:11:27.288
taking the conservative line;
sometimes it was the headman

00:11:27.288 --> 00:11:29.269
taking the conservative line.
 

00:11:29.269 --> 00:11:33.115
It was indeed like a discussion
between a man and say his

00:11:33.115 --> 00:11:37.029
grandfather that was going on
and they will have different

00:11:37.029 --> 00:11:40.668
points of view and individuals
will be different.

00:11:40.668 --> 00:11:45.490
This contact with the ancestors
seems quite natural.

00:11:45.490 --> 00:11:52.587
You read this story--you hear
this story as 'oh my God,' but

00:11:52.587 --> 00:11:57.279
it's perfectly natural to the
people.

00:11:57.279 --> 00:12:00.408
These people in northern Ghana
they have no word for

00:12:00.408 --> 00:12:01.330
supernatural.
 

00:12:01.330 --> 00:12:02.480
It just doesn't exist.
 

00:12:02.480 --> 00:12:04.697
They don't have any--they don't
have scientific explanations for

00:12:04.697 --> 00:12:07.836
anything,
so all explanations are sort of

00:12:07.836 --> 00:12:11.830
somewhere floating around,
some are empirical and

00:12:11.830 --> 00:12:14.443
observational,
and some of them are

00:12:14.443 --> 00:12:17.357
supernatural,
and so there's no boundary

00:12:17.357 --> 00:12:21.168
between these kinds of
explanations for things,

00:12:21.168 --> 00:12:24.936
and so they don't have such a
word and they don't distinguish

00:12:24.936 --> 00:12:29.080
these kinds of discussions with
the ancestors from real things,

00:12:29.080 --> 00:12:32.899
real dreams or daydreams or
anything else.

00:12:32.899 --> 00:12:37.840
It's all a very fluid kind of
thing.

00:12:37.840 --> 00:12:42.445
To people living in that kind
of a culture the Western idea of

00:12:42.445 --> 00:12:46.351
an unwavering set of rules,
cast in stone in some book

00:12:46.351 --> 00:12:49.113
thousands of years ago,
like the Bible,

00:12:49.113 --> 00:12:52.111
like the Koran,
would seem ludicrous to

00:12:52.111 --> 00:12:52.980
Nankana.
 

00:12:52.980 --> 00:12:58.634
To them, our system of a book
that says everything you need to

00:12:58.634 --> 00:13:04.570
know is as crazy as our view of
them talking to the ancestors.

00:13:04.570 --> 00:13:08.139
You should then compare this
kind of individualistic,

00:13:08.139 --> 00:13:12.544
flexible style of religion to
the mass monotheistic religions

00:13:12.544 --> 00:13:16.070
that we have in the northern
temperate zones,

00:13:16.070 --> 00:13:18.759
at least the Western northern
temperate zones.

00:13:18.759 --> 00:13:22.462
These religions are all part of
a big political structure which

00:13:22.462 --> 00:13:25.570
requires uniformity of the
subjects of some king,

00:13:25.570 --> 00:13:29.288
or some emperor,
and submission to that person.

00:13:29.288 --> 00:13:31.048
Of course, as you probably all
know,

00:13:31.048 --> 00:13:36.938
the word Islam itself means
'submission' and the ideal in

00:13:36.938 --> 00:13:40.620
monotheistic religions is
often--

00:13:59.899 --> 00:14:02.340
notice the uniformity.
 

00:14:02.340 --> 00:14:05.320
This is women at prayer and
notice the--

00:14:05.320 --> 00:14:08.072
as you see--when you see a
bigger picture of this there's

00:14:08.072 --> 00:14:11.269
just a sea of women at some big
event all dressed identically,

00:14:11.269 --> 00:14:13.080
all looking identical.
 

00:14:13.080 --> 00:14:17.745
When I was in Morocco I got a
little instruction book that is

00:14:17.745 --> 00:14:20.778
given to children about how to
pray,

00:14:20.778 --> 00:14:24.461
and every detail is specified
down to when you bow down during

00:14:24.461 --> 00:14:27.360
prayer the position of the toes
is specified--

00:14:27.360 --> 00:14:28.850
are they curled under,
are they spread out,

00:14:28.850 --> 00:14:31.308
you have to know that.
 

00:14:31.308 --> 00:14:36.340
Conformity is a very important
part of mass religion.

00:14:36.340 --> 00:14:39.846
Of course in the west how is
conformity enforced in

00:14:39.846 --> 00:14:40.899
Christianity?
 

00:14:40.899 --> 00:14:44.956
You burn the heretics,
a long history of burning and

00:14:44.956 --> 00:14:48.464
killing by the dominant church,
wherever it is,

00:14:48.464 --> 00:14:50.450
you just slaughter the people
that--

00:14:50.450 --> 00:14:53.873
even on very tiny theological
differences if they don't

00:14:53.873 --> 00:14:57.105
believe exactly as the
authorities think they should

00:14:57.105 --> 00:15:00.563
believe,
off with their head,

00:15:00.563 --> 00:15:07.282
so it's a very different kind
of pattern of cultural

00:15:07.282 --> 00:15:14.788
understanding of religion and
ancestors and the world.

00:15:14.788 --> 00:15:20.631
Given this intensity of
devotion to the lineage,

00:15:20.631 --> 00:15:26.350
the main virtue in Africa then
is fertility.

00:15:26.350 --> 00:15:30.950
The main sin is to be barren,
is not have children.

00:15:30.950 --> 00:15:35.907
An inability to have children,
barrenness, is not just a

00:15:35.907 --> 00:15:40.955
passive thing that happens to
you but it's punishment for

00:15:40.955 --> 00:15:44.288
something bad that you have
done.

00:15:44.288 --> 00:15:48.428
There's very little distinction
between infertility,

00:15:48.428 --> 00:15:51.081
the woman just can't get
pregnant, and of course they

00:15:51.081 --> 00:15:54.038
don't accept the idea that it
might be the man's fault,

00:15:54.038 --> 00:15:55.350
but the woman doesn't get
pregnant,

00:15:55.350 --> 00:15:57.610
she's infertile,
she has miscarriages,

00:15:57.610 --> 00:15:59.580
goes partway through the
pregnancy,

00:15:59.580 --> 00:16:01.230
or infant deaths.
 

00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:04.488
The important thing is to have
descendants who can carry on the

00:16:04.488 --> 00:16:07.636
line and however--
whatever the mechanism is by

00:16:07.636 --> 00:16:10.345
which a man or woman,
or the family,

00:16:10.345 --> 00:16:12.950
is incapable of having
descendants,

00:16:12.950 --> 00:16:16.070
that's the worst sin and it's
your fault.

00:16:16.070 --> 00:16:19.009
It's not a passive thing that
happens to you.

00:16:19.009 --> 00:16:24.558
Barren women can be divorced,
they can be shunned,

00:16:24.558 --> 00:16:27.057
and sometimes they need
to--they're not even allowed to

00:16:27.057 --> 00:16:29.139
live in the center of the
village because--

00:16:29.139 --> 00:16:31.283
of course they have no
scientific explanation for

00:16:31.283 --> 00:16:33.404
barrenness,
but maybe it's catching in some

00:16:33.404 --> 00:16:35.235
sense,
either by evil spirits which

00:16:35.235 --> 00:16:38.125
are keeping the woman from
getting pregnant and you don't

00:16:38.125 --> 00:16:40.190
want the evil spirits to attack
you,

00:16:40.190 --> 00:16:46.774
or some other reason they can
often be required to live on the

00:16:46.774 --> 00:16:49.149
edge of the village.
 

00:16:49.149 --> 00:16:52.014
Given this emphasis on,
one way or another,

00:16:52.014 --> 00:16:54.812
getting pregnant,
monogamy is not strictly

00:16:54.812 --> 00:16:58.355
enforced;
it's not the kind of obsession

00:16:58.355 --> 00:17:00.480
that it is in the West.
 

00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:03.451
Here's a wonderful
story--recent 2000,

00:17:03.451 --> 00:17:06.746
this is The People Newspaper
from Nairobi,

00:17:06.746 --> 00:17:07.548
Kenya.
 

00:17:07.548 --> 00:17:11.559
"A group of women stormed
the Kenya police station to

00:17:11.559 --> 00:17:15.853
demand that officers either make
love to them or close illegal

00:17:15.853 --> 00:17:17.118
drinking dens.
 

00:17:17.118 --> 00:17:24.038
They said the drinking made
their husbands impotent.

00:17:24.038 --> 00:17:29.071
The women said the population
of the district was falling off

00:17:29.071 --> 00:17:33.769
as a result of the poor sexual
performance of the men.

00:17:33.769 --> 00:17:37.519
The women,"
it was Kanda actually,

00:17:37.519 --> 00:17:40.326
north of Nairobi,
"brought the businesses in

00:17:40.326 --> 00:17:43.132
town to a halt with their
daylong protest against

00:17:43.132 --> 00:17:45.529
excessive drinking by their men
folk.

00:17:45.529 --> 00:17:48.538
'Our men have turned to
vegetables;

00:17:48.538 --> 00:17:51.098
they leave home early and come
back intoxicated.

00:17:51.098 --> 00:17:53.436
There is no one to meet the
sexual needs of the

00:17:53.436 --> 00:17:57.250
wives.'"
Guess which group it was where

00:17:57.250 --> 00:17:59.548
these women came from?
 

00:17:59.548 --> 00:18:02.808
It was 24 Catholic Church
groups in Kenya.

00:18:02.808 --> 00:18:07.482
They came together and demanded
that the officer in charge of

00:18:07.482 --> 00:18:12.390
the police station order his men
to make love to these women.

00:18:12.390 --> 00:18:17.786
The newspaper discretely does
not say how the police responded

00:18:17.786 --> 00:18:19.288
to this demand.
 

00:18:19.288 --> 00:18:23.523
Now--so the women must be
fertile and the men must be

00:18:23.523 --> 00:18:27.922
believed to be potent or
fertile, of course it's harder

00:18:27.922 --> 00:18:31.180
to tell whether the man is or
isn't.

00:18:31.180 --> 00:18:34.548
The men of course,
in a sense, want to keep the

00:18:34.548 --> 00:18:38.211
fertility of the women for
themselves but it's more

00:18:38.211 --> 00:18:42.386
important to have children no
matter who is the biological

00:18:42.386 --> 00:18:43.338
father.
 

00:18:43.338 --> 00:18:48.068
Not only in the family but once
a child is born,

00:18:48.068 --> 00:18:51.430
perhaps under obviously
uncertain circumstances,

00:18:51.430 --> 00:18:54.009
the village will accept--the
community accepts the children.

00:18:54.009 --> 00:19:00.317
They need people;
they want strength in numbers,

00:19:00.317 --> 00:19:06.126
and so promiscuity is not
frowned on particularly by the

00:19:06.126 --> 00:19:07.500
community.
 

00:19:07.500 --> 00:19:10.269
Everybody knows it goes on and
just keeps quiet.

00:19:10.269 --> 00:19:16.318
I was reading this week and
last a history of a Lesotho.

00:19:16.318 --> 00:19:19.009
How many--Lesotho is a small
country--you've been there?

00:19:19.009 --> 00:19:21.769
No, okay.
 

00:19:21.769 --> 00:19:25.288
A small enclave totally
surrounded by South Africa.

00:19:25.288 --> 00:19:31.348
This was a history before the
Europeans came about the 1700s.

00:19:31.348 --> 00:19:34.019
There was a king then and the
king,

00:19:34.019 --> 00:19:36.920
it was a very small group at
that time,

00:19:36.920 --> 00:19:40.900
not much more than a village,
and when the third son--

00:19:40.900 --> 00:19:44.256
this is sort of a quote,
"When the third son of the

00:19:44.256 --> 00:19:47.795
king died he left a widow who
was still of childbearing age

00:19:47.795 --> 00:19:49.868
but had no surviving children.
 

00:19:49.868 --> 00:19:53.012
By custom the widow should have
gone to live with her husband's

00:19:53.012 --> 00:19:55.903
younger brother so that she
could continue the seed of her

00:19:55.903 --> 00:19:57.068
dead husband."
 

00:19:57.068 --> 00:20:01.428
Exactly as we see in the Old
Testament that we talked about

00:20:01.428 --> 00:20:02.328
last time.
 

00:20:02.328 --> 00:20:05.981
The widow didn't agree and she
went off and actually got

00:20:05.981 --> 00:20:10.098
pregnant by sort of a no good
who wasn't even of that tribe.

00:20:10.098 --> 00:20:16.259
Now this is a real no-no
and--but nevertheless the child,

00:20:16.259 --> 00:20:19.019
since that woman was legally
part of a certain lineage,

00:20:19.019 --> 00:20:23.304
that child by someone who
wasn't even a member of the

00:20:23.304 --> 00:20:28.413
tribe and against the convention
was still accepted as a member

00:20:28.413 --> 00:20:31.048
of the king's lineage there.
 

00:20:31.048 --> 00:20:34.970
It turns that the child of
this--illegitimate in a sense--

00:20:34.970 --> 00:20:38.490
child became the greatest king
that Lesotho has ever known,

00:20:38.490 --> 00:20:44.160
a very important guy named
Moshoeshoe.

00:20:44.160 --> 00:20:48.050
Moshoeshoe himself,
the grandson of the time I'm

00:20:48.050 --> 00:20:51.609
talking about,
he was reputed to have 140 to

00:20:51.609 --> 00:20:52.769
200 wives.
 

00:20:52.769 --> 00:20:54.470
You read the history,
they of course--

00:20:54.470 --> 00:20:56.656
they have whatever written
records they have and the first

00:20:56.656 --> 00:20:58.892
one says well--
when he was young he has 35

00:20:58.892 --> 00:21:03.011
wives, then he has 80 wives,
and every time this is reported

00:21:03.011 --> 00:21:06.144
as he gets older,
and probably accumulates more

00:21:06.144 --> 00:21:08.619
wives,
the number goes up.

00:21:08.619 --> 00:21:10.618
The last report was 200 wives.
 

00:21:10.618 --> 00:21:12.915
Of course we don't know
anything about the accuracy of

00:21:12.915 --> 00:21:13.220
this.
 

00:21:13.220 --> 00:21:17.391
But it was said most of his
latter wives were regarded as

00:21:17.391 --> 00:21:19.028
distinctly inferior.
 

00:21:19.028 --> 00:21:22.641
Moshoeshoe would summon
whomever he wished to spend the

00:21:22.641 --> 00:21:25.717
night with him,
and he undoubtedly sired a vast

00:21:25.717 --> 00:21:26.519
progeny.
 

00:21:26.519 --> 00:21:30.030
He also offered these lesser
wives to visitors for the night

00:21:30.030 --> 00:21:33.157
by way of hospitality,
but according to custom,

00:21:33.157 --> 00:21:36.709
any children these visitors
produced were regarded as

00:21:36.709 --> 00:21:38.690
Moshoeshoe's own children.
 

00:21:38.690 --> 00:21:45.578
Again, in the West,
chastity, monogamy is valued,

00:21:45.578 --> 00:21:48.450
who the father is.
 

00:21:48.450 --> 00:21:52.116
In under-populated cultures,
in cultures that have responded

00:21:52.116 --> 00:21:55.660
to under population it's the
children that are wanted,

00:21:55.660 --> 00:22:00.460
and the mechanism of
biologically fathering a child

00:22:00.460 --> 00:22:02.858
is much less important.
 

00:22:02.858 --> 00:22:05.278
I experienced this myself quite
surprisingly.

00:22:05.278 --> 00:22:08.040
I think I mentioned I had been
in Borneo living with some

00:22:08.040 --> 00:22:10.556
headhunters for a while,
and I got along pretty well

00:22:10.556 --> 00:22:11.740
with the young guys.
 

00:22:11.740 --> 00:22:14.786
Sort of the guys stay together
and so after I was there a

00:22:14.786 --> 00:22:17.670
little bit they offered me their
sisters and said,

00:22:17.670 --> 00:22:21.359
'you shouldn't be sleeping
alone,' and for discretion,

00:22:21.359 --> 00:22:25.538
I won't tell you what happened.
 

00:22:25.538 --> 00:22:30.674
Even nowadays many African
scholars maintain that African

00:22:30.674 --> 00:22:35.902
societies don't even really
distinguish between legitimate

00:22:35.902 --> 00:22:38.470
and illegitimate births.
 

00:22:38.470 --> 00:22:42.890
15% to 25% of women in various
west and east African countries,

00:22:42.890 --> 00:22:46.088
including Kenya for instance,
report premarital births,

00:22:46.088 --> 00:22:50.365
so they may or may not marry
the guy that's there before

00:22:50.365 --> 00:22:51.220
marriage.
 

00:22:51.220 --> 00:22:55.030
As all these estimates of
behavior that is now becoming

00:22:55.030 --> 00:22:58.844
with the Christianization and
the Islamization becoming

00:22:58.844 --> 00:23:03.518
somewhat questionable,
if the official statistics are

00:23:03.518 --> 00:23:08.038
15% to 25% for sure it's a lot
larger than that.

00:23:08.038 --> 00:23:13.814
Of course the husband again
isn't really wildly happy about

00:23:13.814 --> 00:23:20.086
all this playing around and--but
what's most important to him is

00:23:20.086 --> 00:23:21.578
his status.
 

00:23:21.578 --> 00:23:25.308
Again, the biological parentage
of the child is less important.

00:23:25.308 --> 00:23:29.044
He knows whatever child his
wife has will be officially his,

00:23:29.044 --> 00:23:32.400
but he doesn't want to get to
be known as impotent.

00:23:32.400 --> 00:23:35.558
His potency is what matters to
him.

00:23:35.558 --> 00:23:40.017
As long as the woman--and this
happens a lot because very often

00:23:40.017 --> 00:23:43.900
the man is quite significantly
older than the wife,

00:23:43.900 --> 00:23:47.086
especially younger--as he gets
older and accumulates more

00:23:47.086 --> 00:23:48.661
wives,
then younger wives,

00:23:48.661 --> 00:23:51.789
and so his potency may really
be flagging quite a bit,

00:23:51.789 --> 00:23:53.640
so it's a real concern.
 

00:23:53.640 --> 00:23:58.317
As long as--if the wife--as
long as the wife is discreet and

00:23:58.317 --> 00:24:03.074
doesn't make a public display
that this kid is really someone

00:24:03.074 --> 00:24:05.769
else's then not a big problem.
 

00:24:05.769 --> 00:24:09.750
The legal father accepts the
child;

00:24:09.750 --> 00:24:13.808
the community accepts the child.
 

00:24:13.808 --> 00:24:16.108
Anthropologists of course
thought this was very

00:24:16.108 --> 00:24:19.431
interesting and they--
one wonderful--Susan Watkins

00:24:19.431 --> 00:24:22.308
from The University of
Pennsylvania,

00:24:22.308 --> 00:24:26.348
a sociologist,
works in Kenya in the Luo,

00:24:26.348 --> 00:24:28.430
with the Luo on the west of
Kenya;

00:24:28.430 --> 00:24:29.828
Luo people.
 

00:24:29.828 --> 00:24:34.578
She got together a focus group
of women to discuss this issue.

00:24:34.578 --> 00:24:36.685
It's a long thing,
I'll just tell you a little bit

00:24:36.685 --> 00:24:38.612
from it,
and so Susan says,

00:24:38.612 --> 00:24:42.321
"So sometimes women were
unfaithful,"

00:24:42.321 --> 00:24:46.838
pretending a Western
perspective and the women said,

00:24:46.838 --> 00:24:49.624
"Yes being unfaithful
